The paper discusses location privacy issues in cognitive radio networks, which are primarily related to computer networks (cs.NI) and security and privacy (cs.CR). The paper also discusses privacy attacks and countermeasures, which could fall under the category of cybersecurity (cs.CY). Additionally, the paper may involve data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) to implement privacy-preserving techniques. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories are cs.CR and cs.NI, followed by cs.SI, cs.CY, and cs.DS.
